<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="403" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 128]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-05"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your very interesting despatch, of the
                            18th ultimo, in regard to the effect produced by the news of the flight
                            of Lee and the fall of Petersburg and Richmond, and giving translations
                            of the comments of the leading French journals upon the events, has been
                            received.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>